                <p class="mb-4 text-text-light">
                    The application process for APSET 2026 is entirely online. Candidates must visit the official
                    website to register and submit their applications.
                </p>
                <h3 class="font-display text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4 text-text-dark">How to Apply Online:
                </h3>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-text-light">
                    <li><strong class="text-text-dark">Visit Registration Portal:</strong> Go to the <a
                            href="https://apset.aptonline.in/APSET/HomePage.aspx" target="_blank"
                            class="text-accent-teal hover:underline font-semibold">Official APSET Registration
                            Portal</a>.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-text-dark">Application Fee Payment:</strong> Click on "Application Fee
                        Payment" and complete the transaction using Credit Card, Debit Card, or Net Banking.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-text-dark">Check Payment Status:</strong> Once paid, use your Reference ID
                        to "Know Your Payment Status" and ensure success.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-text-dark">Fill Application Form:</strong> Click on "Fill Application Form"
                        to enter personal, academic, and category details.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-text-dark">Document Upload:</strong> Upload scanned photograph and signature
                        as per size specifications.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-text-dark">Submit & Print:</strong> Carefully review the data, submit the
                        form, and "Print Application Form" for future reference.</li>
                </ol>
                <p class="mb-6 text-text-light">

                    last-minute issues.
                </p>

                <h2 id="eligibility"

                    APSET 2026 Eligibility Criteria
                </h2>
                <p class="mb-4 text-text-light">
                    Candidates must fulfil the following eligibility conditions to appear for APSET 2026.
                </p>
                <h3 class="font-display text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4 text-text-dark">Educational
                    Qualifications:</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-text-light">
                    <li>Master's Degree or equivalent from a UGC-recognized university.</li>
                    <li><strong>General/EWS Candidates:</strong> Minimum 55% marks (without rounding off).</li>
                    <li><strong>BC/SC/ST/PWD/Transgender Candidates:</strong> Minimum 50% marks (without rounding off).
                    </li>
                    <li>Candidates who have appeared for their final year Master's examination and are awaiting results
                        are also eligible (must pass within two years).</li>
                    <li>Ph.D. holders who completed their Master's Level examination by September 19, 1991, are eligible
                        for a 5% relaxation in marks (55% to 50%).</li>
                </ul>
                <h3 class="font-display text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4 text-text-dark">Age Limit:</h3>
                <p class="mb-6 text-text-light">

                </p>

                    class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mt-10 mb-6 text-accent-teal border-b-2 border-accent-teal/30 pb-3 animate-slide-in-up">
                    APSET 2026 Examination Pattern
                </h2>
                <p class="mb-4 text-text-light">
                    The APSET examination consists of two papers held in a single day. All questions are objective type
                    (Multiple Choice Questions).
                </p>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6 border border-border-light rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                    <table class="w-full text-left table-auto border-collapse">

                                </th>
                                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-dark font-semibold border-b border-border-light">
                                    Questions</th>
                                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-dark font-semibold border-b border-border-light">Marks
                                </th>
                                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-dark font-semibold border-b border-border-light">Duration
                                </th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="even:bg-primary-bg">
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-border-light text-text-light">Paper-I</td>
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-border-light text-text-light">General Paper
                                    (Teaching & Research Aptitude)</td>
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-border-light text-text-light">50</td>
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-border-light text-text-light">100</td>

                                <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-border-light text-text-light">2 Hours</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>

                <p class="mb-6 text-text-light">
                    There is <strong>no negative marking</strong> for incorrect answers. Paper-I is bilingual (English &

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const stickyHeader = document.getElementById('sticky-header');
            const tocSidebar = document.getElementById('toc-sidebar');
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section[id], h2[id]');
            const tocLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.toc-link');

            const handleScroll = () => {
                const scrollPos = window.scrollY;

                // Sticky Header visibility (Mobile only)
                if (scrollPos > 400) {
                    stickyHeader.classList.remove('-translate-y-full');
                } else {
                    stickyHeader.classList.add('-translate-y-full');
                }

                // TOC Sidebar visibility (Desktop only)
                if (scrollPos > 400) {
                    tocSidebar.style.opacity = '1';
                    tocSidebar.style.pointerEvents = 'auto';
                    tocSidebar.dataset.visible = 'true';
                } else {
                    tocSidebar.style.opacity = '0';
                    tocSidebar.style.pointerEvents = 'none';
                    tocSidebar.dataset.visible = 'false';
                }

                // Active Section tracking
                let currentSectionId = "";
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop - 150;
                    if (scrollPos >= sectionTop) {
                        currentSectionId = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });

                tocLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('text-accent-teal', 'bg-teal-50', 'font-bold');
                    if (link.getAttribute('href') === `#${currentSectionId}`) {
                        link.classList.add('text-accent-teal', 'bg-teal-50', 'font-bold');
                    }
                });
            };

            window.addEventListener('scroll', handleScroll);
            handleScroll(); // Initial check
        });
    </script>
